# Component Architecture

## Code Style

- Arrow functions + `FC<Props>` + default export at end. Props/children: see component-typing.
- TS imports: see fsd-architecture.
- SCSS imports: see styling-guidelines

## 3-Layer Pattern

**Data** (`*-data-layer.tsx`): Stores only. `useStore.use.x()`. Pass to logic. No hooks.
**Logic** (`*-logic-layer.tsx`): Hooks, handlers, state. No stores.
**Presentation** (`*.tsx`): Props only. No hooks.

```typescript
// Data: useStore.use.addExercise(); return <LogicLayer onAdd={...} />;
// Logic: useState, handleSubmit; return <Presentation {...} />;
// Presentation: pure props, className={classes.form}
```

Export: `export { default as X } from 'src/.../x-data-layer'`. No Data → export logic-layer. No Logic → export presentation.

**Skip layers:** No stores → skip Data. No state → skip Logic. Simple → Presentation only.

## File Naming

`component-name-data-layer.tsx`, `component-name-logic-layer.tsx`, `component-name.tsx`, `component-name.module.scss`. See file-naming for kebab-case.
